<TITLE> Siblings die in road accident </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Shirajganj, June 9 (bdnews24.com)  A brother and sister died and 10 others, including the sibling's parents, were injured in a road traffic accident. A roller driver, employed by the Roads and Highways Executive Engineers Department, was also injured in the accident. The accident had happened on the Dhaka-Nalka-Natore road across the western side of the Bangabandhu Bridge, at Kamarkhand upazila of Shirajganj district. Local people said that the accident occurred when a bus collided head on with a Bogra-bound bus on Wednesday morning at 7am. The Bogra-bound bus overturned and six of the injured, including the siblings Nipa and Shourav and their parents, were taken to Shirajganj Sadar Hospital. At around 9.30am, the doctors declared Nipa and Shourav  who came from Kamarkhand upazila - dead. Roller driver Abdul Malek was taken to another clinic in the district. Bangabandhu bridge west-side OC Abdul Jilani told bdnews24.com that the accident happened because of careless and uncontrolled driving. bdn
